# Soft delete

When a project/domain has chosen soft delete, follow `docs/conventions/soft-delete.md`.

Use a nullable timestamp column such as `Date deleted`. Normal application reads should silently exclude deleted rows through service query methods such as `Domain.where { deleted == null }`; callers should not need to remember the filter.

Service delete methods should be explicit and boring: perform required relationship cleanup inline when it is part of the delete contract, then mark `deleted` with GORM/HQL `Domain.executeUpdate(...)`, scoped to tenant/owner where applicable, and constrained with `deleted is null`.

Avoid cascades, archive/deleted mirror tables, PostgreSQL triggers, native SQL helpers, and generic soft-delete frameworks unless the user/project explicitly asks for that approach. If code needs deleted rows, make that an explicit query path rather than weakening normal list/get methods.
